This paper focuses on learning object representations for control and reinforcement learning tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of keypoints for tracking objects and object parts, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses reinforcement learning to control keypoint locations, which is a topic in both machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
